rest_of_day_open: I see myself taking some time out of the weekend to reevaluate some of my finances and options of where to distribute my money. I also see myself going to play tennis and having a generally productive rest of the week, whether that be staying active or learning how to cook a new recipe
critical_positive: I think what worked well was the fact that we were both Chinese Americans who had much of the same cultural experiences growing up in a small town that is predominantly white and eventually becoming more cosmopolitan as we went into college and then into the workforce. I think backgrounds being alike definitely helped us connect
critical_negative: What didn't work well was the fact that my conversation partner was a lot older than me and therefore all we could really talk about were some of our similarities. It was hard to bring up any interests or memes/jokes because I figured it would be met with an awkward silence

rest_of_day_open: Starting on Monday, my week will be very busy as my work will begin to exponentially increase as all of the financials at my company will be closed and we will need to get them finalized to present to the executives.  However, I think it will be manageable and I will still be able to get my work done as well as have time for my family.  For the weekend, we will try to get some social distanced outdoor park time.
critical_positive: I think what worked well is despite us being in different times of our lives, we grew up with the same trajectory.  I was able to relate with my partner on their journey from adolescence to adulthood.  This helped spur the conversation on and I was able to speak and listen intently on this topic.  In addition, I think as I had more experience, I was able to give unsolicited advice for my "past me" to help them.
critical_negative: I think my partner had a bit of anxiety talking to strangers so it was difficult to get them to speak more openly and have a healthy dialogue between the two of us.  I was having to come up with topics for them to speak on so they would actually talk to me and have something to talk about.  This made the parts where there was a small amount of dead time very slow and somewhat awkward.
